            "brief_summary": "RATIONALE: Hormone therapy may be an effective treatment for prostate cancer.\n\nPURPOSE: Randomized phase III trial to evaluate the effectiveness of treatment with flutamide and suramin with or without hydrocortisone in men who have metastatic or recurrent prostate cancer.",
            "eligibility_criteria": "DISEASE CHARACTERISTICS: Histologically confirmed adenocarcinoma of the prostate that is stage D2 Measurable or evaluable disease required with at least one of the following: At least 7 bone lesions Visceral involvement No more than 50% replacement of liver by tumor No clinical suspicion of brain me",
